@node help
@subsection @option{-help}

@kindex -help
Produce a summary of the options available to the assembler.  There is a
side-effect of the clang driver, that this option cannot be specified using
@option{-Wa}. For example
@example
clang -Wa,-help
@end example

will just complain about the lack of input files.  The reason is that the
driver just passes @option{-Wa} options to the assembler, without any knowledge
of what they do.  It thus thinks @command{clang} has been invoked without any
file to process, so prints out the error message.

Instead you should explicitly invoke the assembler backend
(@pxref{cc1as,,invoking the assembler directly}:
@example
clang -cc1as -help
@end example

